#DOC id=14--social-approvals-posts source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/14--social-approvals-posts.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.300Z

S|# 14 · Social Approvals (Posts)|> Everything regarding posts: for each post idea, Leonardo generates 8 images and William drafts A/B copy; the owner clicks an image and posts now or schedules. Sidebar badge: 6 pending.
S|Purpose|The ap surface for soc posts. For each post, the system presents generated imagery and copy variants so the owner just **picks and approves** — then posts immediately or sends it to the Scheduler. This is one of the main feeders of the dec Queue (the "ap all three LinkedIn posts" type items).
S|Page header|- Title: **soc Approvals**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / soc Approvals`. // - A "X of Y in the queue" progress indicator and **rv each** / batch controls. // - Top bar: **System healthy**, **agents live**. // - Sidebar badge shows the pending count (**6**).
S|The post under review|- **Post ctx header** — e.g. *"Instagram post · from 'Claude ran my business'"* with a "1 of 3 in the experiment" indicator and a "Leonardo generated 8 images" note. // - **Copy variants (A/B)** — two text columns prepared by **William** (copywriting agt): //   - **Variant A** and **Variant B**, each the full caption (e.g. "I gave one business to a team of AI agents for 7 days. Here's exactly what shipped, what broke…"), so the owner can choose the stronger hook. Marked **recommended** on one. /
S|Actions|- **Post now** — publish immediately to the platform. // - **Schedule** — push to the **Scheduler** (`15`) to place on the posting calendar. // - ap/skip controls to move through the queue; batch ap (e.g. ap all three in an experiment).
S|Agents involved|- **Leonardo** — generates the 8 candidate images (Asset Lab). // - **William** — drafts the A/B caption variants. // - Henry escalates pending approvals into the **dec Queue**.
S|Workflow|Post idea → Leonardo (8 images) + William (A/B copy) → owner picks image + copy → **Post now** or **Schedule** → appears on the Scheduler calendar and later in soc anl.